Its value is much better than iPad. The build is solid. The specification is reasonable.

The price for HD 8 is about the same as in the states.
I would have chosen HD 10 instead had its price been reasonable.

Keep in mind that this is not an ordinary tablet.
Its OS is modified by Amazon.

It does not come with Google Play Store. You have to figure out how to install it if you want Google Play. If the installation button is not responding, try to reboot.

When the screen is locked, it displays advertisements.

I bought this to replace my iPad 2. I use it mostly to watch YouTube and as an ebook reader. 

Chinese cheap tablets might appear to have better specifications than Fire.
However, Chinese specifications might be fake.
Even Taiwanese brand Tablets are made in China these days.
Hence, I choose Amazon over no name tablets.

Although Fire HD 8 is not perfect, I am happy with its performance and price.
